cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NA 

This paper deals with image reconstruction using sparsity exploiting methods, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves promoting sparsity in the wavelet and graph gradient domains, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses computational efficiency, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
